The paper deals with valued constraint satisfaction problems (VCSPs), which are a generalisation of constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and maximum constraint satisfaction problems (Max-CSPs). This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG), which are all concerned with solving computational problems. Additionally, the paper uses linear programming as a tool to solve VCSPs, which is a common technique in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
